{{Quote|There's a shipping company just outside of Mos Eisley called White Thranta. I have information that leads me to believe they aren't a simple shipping company.|[[Reimos Taligg]], to a spacer|<ref name="SWG:DI" />}}
'''White Thranta Shipping Company''', also known as '''White Thranta Shipping''', or simply '''White Thranta''', was a small shipping company based on [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]] during the [[Imperial Era/Legends|Imperial Era]]. In fact, the company was a front for illegal activities of [[Jabba's criminal empire/Legends|Jabba the Hutt's criminal empire]].

==Description==
{{Quote|White Thranta Shipping delivers to most of the known galaxy.|An advertisement for the White Thranta Shipping Company|<ref name="SWG:SD" />}}
Officially, the White Thranta Shipping Company was established by a consortium of Tatooine business owners seeking to meet a demand for secure galaxy-wide shipping. The company was specialized in shipping hazardous materials to most of the known galaxy.<ref name="SWG:SD" />

The White Thranta Shipping Company had [[White Thranta Shipping offices|headquarters]] located not far outside of the city of [[Mos Eisley/Legends|Mos Eisley]], on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] of Tatooine.<ref name="SWG:SD" /> The company was ostensibly legitimate,<ref name="TCSWE" /> despite it was actually a cover for [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba the Hutt's]] criminal activities. A large number of security guards were hired, for security as well as to make sure no one found out what they were really doing deep in the confines of their bunker.<ref name="SWG:DI" /> The security personnel of the White Thranta used a modified version of a popular [[Sg-82 sonic rifle]].<ref name="WTR">{{SWGTCG|set=The Nightsister's Revenge|cardname=White Thranta Rifle}}</ref>

==History==
{{Quote|I have been watching the progress of subject 23. While the stim he was administered was a failure, the resulting mutation created sores that seep a highly contagious viral agent.|White Thranta internal medical report.|<ref name="SWG:DI" />}}
[[File:WhiteThrantaHQ.jpg|thumb|left|250px|The [[White Thranta Shipping offices|White Thranta Shipping bunker]].]]
During the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], the White Thranta served as a [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggling]] base of operations and most of the goods shipped were destined to the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]].<ref name="TCSWE" /> People involved with the White Thranta criminal activities included [[Bib Fortuna/Legends|Bib Fortuna]], [[Ree-Yees/Legends|Ree-Yees]], [[Kane Ezruud]], [[Kaazo Barrezz]], [[Carh'la Bastra]], [[Kosto Maggio]] and [[Manu Rippodo]].<ref name="SWG:DI" />

By the time of the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], members of the White Thranta Shipping Company got involved in more questionable activities. [[Brok Ziam]] and [[Durr Roddack]] started steal money to the company, that is to say to Jabba,<ref name="SWG:SO" /> in order to conduct medical experiments. They performed unethical experiments on sapient races in the bunker bellow the White Thranta offices,<ref name="SWG:DP">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=class|Legacy|Data Purge|Tatooine}}</ref> without Jabba being aware of it.<ref name="SWG:JDW">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=class|Legacy|Jabba's Dirty Work|Tatooine}}</ref> In total, White Thranta had kidnapped and infected at least 41 victims for medical experiment, including [[Dakk Jenzik]], [[Leon Kovalski]], [[Tork Magzyn]] and a woman named [[Dina (individual)|Dina]].<ref name="SWG:DI" />

[[File:WhiteThranta3.jpg|thumb|right|250px|The deep recesses of the headquarters offered a glimpse of illegal experimentation in one of the complex's medical bays.]]
In [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]],<ref name="SWG_timeline">{{SWG_timeline}}</ref> Jabba's employee [[Reimos Taligg]] figured out something went wrong in the White Thranta bunker and tasked a spacer to slice the computers of the company, eventually discovering the situation.<ref name="SWG:DI" /> Reimos then requested the spacer with questioning Durr Roddack. Roddack refused to cooperate, forcing the spacer to kill him. Using information found on Durr's datapad and personal computer, Reimos then discovered Brok Ziam was resposible of the complete operation. Ziam refused to surrender and was finnaly killed by the spacer.<ref name="SWG:SO" />

In the meantime, a [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] went to the White Thranta offices in order to execute the indebted [[Untas]].<ref name="SWG:FJ">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=class|Bounty Hunter|Faeto's Job|Tatooine}}</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
The White Thranta Shipping Company appeared in the [[2003]] [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[Star Wars Galaxies]]'', a [[Wikipedia:Massively multiplayer online role-playing game|massively multiplayer online roleplaying game]], a massively multiplayer online roleplaying game developed by [[Sony]] Online Entertainment and published by [[LucasArts]],<ref name="SWG:SD" /> prior to its closure on [[December 15]], [[2011]].<ref name="Shutdown">{{SonyCite|url=playerinfo|text=IMPORTANT INFORMATION ABOUT ''STAR WARS'' GALAXIES™}}</ref> The White Thranta Shipping Company was added to the game as part of the "[[W:c:swg:Legacy Quest|Legacy Quest]]" with the release of the "[[W:c:swg:Publish 25 Notes for November 15, 2005|Publish 25]]," a.k.a. the "[[W:c:swg:New Game Enhancements|New Game Enhancements]]," on [[November 15]], [[2005]].<ref name="SonyCite-Publish Archive 2005">{{SonyCite|url=players/content.vm?id=64886&resource=publish|text=Publish Archive 2005}}</ref>

In the cut quests "Opening Moves" and "Information Control," the [[Trandoshan/Legends|Trandoshan]] [[Aigorn]] would have tasked the player with eliminating one of the medical staff in the White Thranta infirmary and steal medical data. The company is known as White Horse in game files pertaining to this quest.<ref name="File1">{{GalaxiesNGE}} &mdash; tatooine_eisley_epidemic.stf, tatooine_eisley_aigorn.stf, tatooine_eisley_information_control.stf</ref> In another cut quest, the woman [[Kashi VanDeef]] would have requested the player to rescue her husband [[Pilar VanDeef|Pilar]] from the White Thranta.<ref name="File2">{{GalaxiesNGE}} &mdash; tatooine_eisley_kashi.stf</ref>

